- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is relevant as the paper discusses auto-completion of host attribute configurations. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is relevant as the paper may involve the use of programming languages for expressing security policies and invariants. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with network security policies and information flow security strategies.
